26/02/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- An international conference on the challenges facing Kosovo after declaring independence was held in Tirana on Monday (February 25th). US Ambassador to Albania John Withers addressed the forum and said Kosovo is on the right road to establishing a strong democracy. He also indicated that Washington would be ready to channel 269m euros in economic aid to Kosovo in coming months. (Balkanweb, Top-Channel, Albanian President website - 25/02/08) 
